"title": "5279: crowds",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5279: crowds",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Multitudes of people feature prominently in the narrative parts of Scripture, particularly in the Gospels and Acts. The attitudes of the crowds to Jesus Christ throw light on his ministry, as do his attitudes to them.</p>\n<h2>Crowds tend towards evil</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:2\">EXO 23:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:2\">PSA 64:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:6\">ISA 53:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:2\">JER 9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:42\">EZK 23:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:8-Mark15:15\">MRK 15:8–15:15</a></p>\n<h2>Crowds and worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:4\">PSA 42:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a></p>\n<h2>God's judgment is pronounced on crowds of people</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:11-Ezek7:14\">EZK 7:11–7:14</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:14\">JOL 3:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Multitudes are seen by John in his vision</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a></strong> <em>The redeemed in heaven</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:15\">REV 17:15</a></strong> <em>Sinful people on earth.</em></p>\n<h2>Crowds played a large part in Jesus Christ's ministry</h2>\n<p>Gathering round him:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:2\">MAT 13:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:1\">MRK 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:4\">LUK 8:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:20\">MRK 3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:21\">MRK 5:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:1\">LUK 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:1\">MAT 8:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:7\">MRK 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:25\">LUK 14:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:2\">JHN 6:2</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a> <em>running to the scene of his healings</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:42\">LUK 8:42</a> <em>almost crushing him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:7\">LUK 3:7</a> <em>coming to him to be baptised</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:30\">MAT 15:30</a> <em>bringing people to him to be healed</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a> <em>eating with him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:34\">JHN 12:34</a> <em>questioning him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:17\">JHN 12:17</a> <em>spreading news of him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:12\">JHN 7:12</a> <em>whispering about him</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ often taught crowds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:13\">MRK 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:25-Matt5:2\">MAT 4:25–5:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:17-Luke6:20\">LUK 6:17–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:7\">MAT 11:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:24\">LUK 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:1-Matt13:3\">MAT 13:1–13:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:1-Mark4:3\">MRK 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:4-Luke8:5\">LUK 8:4–8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:34\">MAT 13:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:10\">MAT 15:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:14\">MRK 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:1\">MAT 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:34\">MRK 6:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:1\">MRK 10:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ had compassion on the crowds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:36\">MAT 9:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:34\">MRK 6:34</a></p>\n<h3>He healed them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:14\">MAT 14:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:2\">MAT 19:2</a></p>\n<h3>He fed them</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:15-Matt14:21\">MAT 14:15–14:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:35-Mark6:44\">MRK 6:35–6:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:12-Luke9:17\">LUK 9:12–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:5-John6:13\">JHN 6:5–6:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32-Matt15:38\">MAT 15:32–15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:1-Mark8:10\">MRK 8:1–8:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's other contacts with crowds</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:55\">MAT 26:55</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:48\">MRK 14:48</a> <em>questioning them</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:23-Matt9:25\">MAT 9:23–9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:4\">MRK 2:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:19\">LUK 5:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:22\">MAT 14:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:45\">MRK 6:45</a> <em>dismissing them</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:30\">LUK 4:30</a> <em>passing through them</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:36\">MRK 4:36</a> <em>leaving them</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:13\">JHN 5:13</a> <em>slipping away from them</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:33\">MRK 7:33</a> <em>leading a man away from the crowd to heal him</em></p>\n<h2>Individuals mentioned in connection with a crowd</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17\">MRK 9:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:37-Luke9:40\">LUK 9:37–9:40</a> <em>the man with a demon-possessed son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:21-Mark5:34\">MRK 5:21–5:34</a> <em>Jairus and the woman with a haemorrhage</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:12\">LUK 7:12</a> <em>the widow with a dead son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:2-Luke19:3\">LUK 19:2–19:3</a> <em>Zaccheus, unable to see Jesus Christ because of the crowd</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:46-Mark10:48\">MRK 10:46–10:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35-Luke18:39\">LUK 18:35–18:39</a> <em>blind Bartimaeus, rebuked by the crowd and healed by Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:27\">LUK 11:27</a> <em>the woman who blessed Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:3-John5:9\">JHN 5:3–5:9</a> <em>the man, in the crowd of disabled people by the pool, whom Jesus Christ healed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:42\">JHN 11:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:17\">JHN 12:17</a></p>\n<h2>The crowds' varied reactions to Jesus Christ's teaching</h2>\n<h3>Awe, amazement, delight and faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:8\">MAT 9:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:22\">MRK 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:37\">MRK 12:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:31\">JHN 7:31</a></p>\n<h3>Accusation, confusion and questioning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:20\">JHN 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:29\">JHN 12:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:34\">JHN 12:34</a></p>\n<h2>Crowds played a large part in the final events of Jesus Christ's life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:46\">MAT 21:46</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:12\">MRK 12:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:19\">LUK 20:19</a> <em>Fear of the crowds restrained the Jewish leaders.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:8-Matt21:11\">MAT 21:8–21:11</a> <em>Crowds demonstrated on Jesus Christ's entry into Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:8-Mark15:15\">MRK 15:8–15:15</a> <em>The crowd, stirred up by the chief priests, asked for the release of Barabbas</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a> <em>Pilate washed his hands in front of the crowd</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47\">MAT 26:47</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43\">MRK 14:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:47\">LUK 22:47</a> <em>A crowd came with Judas to Gethsemane.</em></p>\n<h2>A crowd gathered in Jerusalem at Pentecost</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:6\">ACT 2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:14\">ACT 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Crowds featured prominently in the ministry of the apostles</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:16\">ACT 5:16</a> <em>bringing the sick to be healed</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:6\">ACT 8:6</a> <em>listening to Philip's preaching in Samaria</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:44-Acts13:45\">ACT 13:44–13:45</a> <em>listening to Paul and Barnabas in Pisidian Antioch</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:11-Acts14:19\">ACT 14:11–14:19</a> <em>attempting to worship Paul and Barnabas in Lystra</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:22\">ACT 16:22</a> <em>attacking Paul and Silas in Philippi</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:5-Acts17:13\">ACT 17:5–17:13</a> <em>being stirred up against Paul in Thessalonica and Berea</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:30-Acts19:35\">ACT 19:30–19:35</a> <em>rising up against Paul in Ephesus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:27-Acts21:40\">ACT 21:27–21:40</a> <em>rising up against Paul in Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:22\">ACT 22:22</a> <em>giving Paul a limited hearing in Jerusalem</em></p>\n<h2>Crowds as the source of loud noise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:4\">ISA 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:6\">DAN 10:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:1\">REV 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:6\">REV 19:6</a></p>",
